	<div class='container main'>

	<h1>Travel Directions</h1>

	Here's all the info you might need to get to the convention site!

	<div class="vspace"></div>

	<ul>
		<li>
			A. Ruzettelaan 195, Blankenberge (<a 
				href='https://www.google.be/maps/dir/Duinse+Polders,+A.+Ruzettelaan+195,+8370+Blankenberge//@51.3182306,3.1503646,14.75z/data=!4m13!4m12!1m5!1m1!1s0x47c4aa6f033c08b3:0x994058b684b08c8e!2m2!1d3.1539307!2d51.3202384!1m5!1m1!1s0x47c4aa6f033c08b3:0x994058b684b08c8e!2m2!1d3.1539307!2d51.3202384'
				>Google maps</a>)
		</li>
		<li>
			GPS: 51°19'12.9"N 3°09'13.7"E
		</li>
	</ul>

	<div class="vspace"></div>

	For attendees coming from abroad, we suggest you to plan your trip from Brussels to Blankenberge with the website of the official transport company: 
	<a href="http://www.belgianrail.be/en/">http://www.belgianrail.be/en/</a>.

	<div class="vspace"></div>

	<a href='pics/map.png'><img class='minimap' src='pics/minimap.png'/></a>

	<h2>From abroad</h2>

	<h3>...by plane</h3>
	<ul>
		<li>
			<span class='highlight'>Brussels National Airport (Zaventem)</span>
			<ul>
				<li>Take the intercity train (IC36 La Panne) to Brussels South station</li>
				<li>Take the intercity train (IC15 Blankenberge) to the last station</li>
			</ul>
		</li>
		<li>
			<span class='highlight'>Charleroi Airport (Brussels South)</span>
			<ul>
				<li>Take the shuttle (<a href='https://www.brussels-city-shuttle.com/en#/'>reservation needed!</a>) to Brussels South station</li>
				<li>Take the intercity train (IC15 Blankenberge) to the last station</li>
			</ul>
		</li>
	</ul>
	<h3>...by High Speed Train</h3>
	There are two high-speed trains companies serving Brussels:
	<ul>
		<li><a href='https://www.thalys.com/be/en/'>Thalys</a> (France-Belgium-Netherlands-Germany)</li>
		<li><a href='https://www.b-europe.com/EN/Trains/ICE'>ICE</a> (Belgium-Netherlands-Germany-Austria-Switzerland)</li>
	</ul>
	Step out at Brussels South and take the intercity train (IC15 Blankenberge) to the last station.


	<h2>From Belgium</h2>
	<h3>...by public transports</h3>
	From Brussels, take the train direction <span class='highlight'>Knokke-Blankenberge</span> to Blankenberge station. Be careful, that train is split in Brugge.
	<br/>
	Then:
	<ul>
		<li>On foot: 25 minutes from the station, simply follow <span class='highlight'>Koning-Albert-I-Laan</span> (King-Albert-the-First Lane).</li>
		<li>With the tram: take the <span class='highlight'>De Panne-Oostende-Knokke</span> tram right in front of the station (every 15 minutes). Step out at the third stop <span class='highlight'>Blankenberge Duinse Polders</span> and you're right in front of the hotel.</li>
	</ul>

